            <p>Friend <addressee>I. Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p>In the Name of our <add>?</add> congregation<lb/> we thank you heartily for your
                kind<lb/> wishes and the <sic>trubel</sic> you have taken<lb/> in our
                    <sic>behalfe</sic>. I have written to<lb/>
                <persName>Mr Jas Einstein</persName> for that Sephis<lb/> will direction how to send
                it.<lb/> Our diversion seems to gain daily<lb/> friends on both <sic>sites</sic>,
                that is to<lb/> say, the feeling towards us by these<lb/> Reformers, is very bitter,
                and<lb/> I fear very much that the children<lb/> even on both <sic>sites</sic> will
                cultivate<lb/> bad feelings, because <sic>the</sic> hear<lb/> it from their Parents.
                I try all I can<lb/> to, to <add>?</add> these things and will<lb/> not permit it in
                my Family, yet<lb/> such is the fact in other <sic>Familys</sic>.â€”</p>
            <p>Hoping this will reach you all well<lb/> with many kind regards</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Yours Respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">J Laufirt<add>?</add></persName>
            </p>
